pr_review_comment_body:
You could optimize distance calculation, at least the common case, by:
```cython
from libc.math import fabs

cdef inline double manhattan(double a, double b):
    return fabs(a - b)

def fastdtw(..., dist=None):
    ...
    if dist is None:
        dist = manhattan
    ...

Have you considered using a loop to make the code more concise? You could make it like:
```
aMaxAge = Encoding::BigEndian::HostSwap32(aMaxAge);
coapOption.mLength = 0;
do
{
    buf[coapOption.mLength] = aMaxAge & 0xff;
    aMaxAge = aMaxAge >> 8;
    coapOption.mLength++;
} while (aMaxAge != 0 && coapOption.mLength < sizeof(buf))
```
You could even make an generic function from it and use in both, AppendMaxAgeOption and AppendObserveOption.
